{
  "doc_id": "18729",
  "text": "Vitamin D receptor (VDR) is a nuclear transcription factor, a member of the steroid/ thyroid hormone receptor family, which mediates the physiological actions of its hormone ligand, 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D 3 [CITATION_1] . VDR is expressed in a large variety of mammalian cells from almost every tissue that has been examined thus far. VDR is also present in numerous fresh cancer cells and in a variety of cancer cell lines, as well as in various kinds of hematopoietic cells and leukemic cell lines [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
